##Get the 5G into Vulcan Mountain! Urgent Reconstruction of logistics chain behind the aid of Wuhan

Micro-signal Lengjing

Feature Introduction, tencent news product column, "Prism" focus on financial in-depth reports.

By Luo Songsong editor Zhang Qingning
Production | prism tencent Xiaoman studio

Welcome to download tencent news APP for more quality information

At a press conference held on January 30, Health Commission spokesman Mi Feng said that according to the current needs of the epidemic response, truck drivers transporting supplies to Hubei Province need to take necessary protective measures, after return, no fever, cough and other symptoms, allowing them to continue to transport supplies.

This is the news that logistics enterprise wants to hear most.

After Wuhan announced the closure of the city, more than 20 batches of supplies were sent to the affected area, and more than 40 drivers were sent, according to employees at a large courier company. "Due to the need to prevent and control the epidemic, these drivers must be quarantined when they return, " they said

"They were on holiday and saw the group calling for help, signing up as volunteers, not taking any money and taking risks. But after returning from Wuhan, there will be a 14-day quarantine, in which case there will be fewer and fewer drivers who volunteer and there will be a bigger and bigger capacity gap,"the employee said.

Over the past week or so, materials from all over the country are being urgently transported to Hubei epidemic areas such as Wuhan. It is the Spring Festival holiday, and most transport companies are just "half closed" . The transportation resources that can be mobilized are already limited, segregation has exacerbated the lack of transport capacity.

Health Commission's above statement is expected to ease the contradiction between supply and demand for transport capacity.

To Transport 5G equipment into Vulcan Mountain

Yan Dongfang is a driver for Debon express and a native of Wuhan.

At around 1:00 a.m. on New Year's Eve, he received a call from the head of the Wuhan Motorcade, asking him to pick up a car from Beijing in the morning. The car was carrying 5G communication equipment donated to the Huoshenshan Hospital, and he was anxious to wait for it to be installed.

On the first day of the Lunar New Year, Yan Dongfang drove a 9.6-meter van to the East West Lake Toll Station in Wuhan, "supplies were already arriving in Wuhan, and we had to go to the expressway to meet them, either because they couldn't get in or because they were reluctant to get in because of the epidemic. "

According to Yan Dongfang, Debang set up a special task force on New Year's Eve night, the deployment of transport capacity to transport anti-epidemic materials, driver shortage is a thorny issue.

Debon Express Wuhan branch although there are more than 300 trucks available for dispatch, the first two days of the New Year, only three drivers can go, the third day of the fourth day increased to eight drivers, currently a total of 12 drivers, most from Wuhan and surrounding cities.

The drivers had to work round the clock because of the large amount of supplies waiting to be delivered.

"On the morning of January 29, two drivers took a group of medical and protective materials from Wuhan to Shiyan, 400 kilometers away, and returned overnight at around 7 a.m. on January 30, " Yan said.

Shi Jun, secretary-general of the Wuhan Logistics Association, said that at present, medical supplies are flowing smoothly into Wuhan, "If the material is earmarked for donation to the Red Cross, the Red Cross will make a unified allocation. If not, we can coordinate point-to-point docking and then ship it to institutions such as hospitals. "

On January 28, Yan Dongfang also sent a batch of hotpot donated by Haidilao to Wuhan Jinyintan Hospital,

"When we arrived at the hospital, the head nurse saw that we were wearing ordinary masks. She went back to the room and took out 10 medical masks and a bottle of hand sanitizer. She told us to take care of our protection. Also coming out to receive supplies were medical staff members in camouflage uniforms, who looked tired and had bloodshot eyes, " Yan said, "All we can do is get supplies to where they are most needed without delay. "

In response to the shortage of drivers, the debang Wuhan Company has reported to the higher authorities, "On the one hand, we are actively communicating with drivers, and on the other hand, we are reporting to the Public Security Bureau some drivers who are willing to come back so that they can return to their posts as soon as possible. "

Coping with structural strain

The outbreak coincided with the Spring Festival period, the vast majority of logistics companies in the "semi-closed" state.

The head of a courier company said to us that the employees of the company's functional departments had a holiday on January 16, while the couriers and drivers had a holiday on the 19th, "We need to coordinate drivers by region to return to work when we take on the transportation needs of the aid, and give priority to the transportation of the network which can send the whole vehicle to donate the aid. "

A person in charge of a medical consumables company in Henan told us that no matter the raw materials are transported in or the finished products of medical protection are transported out, there are problems in transportation.

"The epidemic prevention authorities do have concerns that the movement of vehicles and people will increase the difficulty of epidemic prevention, while the drivers are worried that there are more checkpoints for epidemic monitoring on the roads and traffic will be impeded, which will affect the efficiency of transportation, " the official said, the issue is not whether a particular site or platform is open, but whether the entire logistics system needs to be coordinated."

On the one hand is the unceasing material transportation demand, on the other hand is unable to return to duty in time the driver, this causes the transportation capacity supply and demand contradiction to be more prominent.

Jiang Guojun (not his real name) is the boss of a freight company in Shanghai. The company had a collective holiday on January 21, and the trucks stayed in Shanghai.

On January 29, he showed us a screenshot of the chat. Screenshots show a shipment of five tons of medical supplies destined for the Dongxihu Toll Station in Wuhan from Linyi in Shandong Province, with an offer of up to 45,000 yuan, and a clear message in the special needs column: "Only in, no out, and so on. "

Jiang believes that in this situation, on the one hand, many drivers have gone home and will not be able to return to work for a while. On the other hand, some drivers are worried about the epidemic and may be quarantined or detained in Wuhan.

In view of the structural transport capacity tension, dozens of logistics companies have opened green channels, and open storage resources.

January 28th, fuyou truck, Shiqiao transport capacity, Zei 1, Huaneng smart chain, good luck, Chiwan East, one meter Tita, foal, full vehicle, truck baby, fast dog taxi, cargo pull, Flash Send, G7 and other 17 logistics platforms launched a joint operation, to come to Hubei's aid.

SF Airways to carry Kaifeng

Due to the closure of cities and traffic restrictions in Hubei Province, there is some uncertainty in the timeliness of land transport, at which time air cargo shows its own advantages.

A number of Henan Medical Supplies Company officials told us that over the past week, they sent medical supplies to Hubei and all over the country, go are SF, "SF express courier and outlets are still open. "

On January 24, a local plane carrying the three truckloads of medical protection materials from Rizhao, Shandong, was canceled after a local plane was scheduled to depart from Rizhao. The relay was being carried by a cargo plane from Shunfeng, which was docked in Linyi, Shandong.

A cargo plane carrying medical masks and other medical supplies from SF arrived at Wuhan Tianhe Airport on Jan. 24, the first day the Han corridor was closed.

From January 24 to 26, two Special Planes Take off from Shenzhen and Hangzhou every day.

Since January 27, SF express has added a beijing-wuhan special plane, and from January 29, a new Weifang-wuhan special plane. To the 29th, a total of 16 planes have landed in Wuhan Tianhe Airport, the cumulative delivery of medical, rescue and other urgently needed supplies more than 354 tons.

We also learned that on January 30, five SF flights arrived in Wuhan carrying about 120 tons of medical and protective materials, one of which took off from Narita International Airport, Tokyo, Japan.

Cargo Airline is China's largest airline with a fleet of 58 aircraft, including two double decker Boeing 747.

The relevant person in charge of the Shunfeng Hubei Company said to us that in order to speed up and increase the distribution of relief materials, nearly 100 outlets in the city of Wuhan in Shunfeng, Hubei have resumed business one after another, staff at all levels to take the initiative to communicate with the local prevention and Control Headquarters and other government departments, voluntary return to work to participate in material transportation and distribution.

In addition to SF Airways, China Post Express, China Eastern Airlines, Air China, hna and Yantong airlines have opened air green channel to support Wuhan.
